JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s President Jacob Zuma has appointed Justice Mandisa Maya as the President of the Supreme Court of Appeal, the president&#8217;s office said on Friday, making her the first woman to occupy the position.&#8220;Her appointment to the position elevates her to the third highest position in the Judicial Branch, after the Chief Justice and Deputy Chief Justice of the Republic,&#8221; Zuma said.